      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:8:1:50:27",
      "text": [
        " كَانَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ (صلى الله عليه وآله) لَا يَتَدَاوَى مِنَ الزُّكَامِ وَ يَقُولُ مَا مِنْ أَحَدٍ إِلَّا وَ بِهِ عِرْقٌ مِنَ الْجُذَامِ فَإِذَا أَصَابَهُ الزُّكَامُ قَمَعَهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473712\">H 15024</a> – A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Bakr bin Salih, and Al-Nowfali, and someone else with an unbroken chain going up to Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, the following:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-a\">A</span>bu Abdullah</span><sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘The Rasool Allah<sup>saww</sup> never used to cure himself<sup>saww</sup> from the flu, and would say: ‘There is no one except that he has a vein from the leprosy, so if he is struck by the flu, it suppresses it’. "
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "578. Muhammad Bin yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Salim, who has narrated the following: ‘Abu Abdullah (a.s.) has said; ‘The Rasool Allah (saww) said: ‘The flu is an army from the armies of Allah (azwj) Mighty and Majestic. Allah (azwj) Mighty and Majestic Sends it to the illness, to eradicate it’."
        ]
      }
    },
